{"article_id":"oajRQw4B7kUbhWrh","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"The 2012 terrorist assault on the U.S. diplomatic post in Benghazi , Libya , involved attackers from several major international terrorist networks ,","depth":7},{"id":1,"text":"according to a bipartisan Senate report","depth":9},{"id":2,"text":"released Wednesday","depth":9},{"id":3,"text":"that blames the intelligence community and the State Department","depth":10},{"id":4,"text":"- and Ambassador J. Christopher Stevens himself -","depth":10},{"id":5,"text":"for lapses .","depth":9},{"id":6,"text":"Mr. Stevens and three other Americans died in the attack ,","depth":8},{"id":7,"text":"which","depth":10},{"id":8,"text":"the report by the Senate Select Committee on Intelligence said","depth":10},{"id":9,"text":"could have been averted","depth":10},{"id":10,"text":"if the State Department had heeded numerous warnings .","depth":10},{"id":11,"text":"But Mr. Stevens himself rejected Defense Department offers of more security ,","depth":9},{"id":12,"text":"and he never forwarded other warnings from Benghazi to his superiors in Washington ,","depth":9},{"id":13,"text":"the report concluded .","depth":8},{"id":14,"text":"The 85-page report directly contradicts a New York Times investigation last month","depth":6},{"id":15,"text":"that argued","depth":7},{"id":16,"text":"no international terrorist groups were involved in the assault ,","depth":8},{"id":17,"text":"which","depth":10},{"id":18,"text":"the paper said","depth":10},{"id":19,"text":"was spurred , in part , by an anti-Islam video .","depth":9},{"id":20,"text":"Committee members ,","depth":8},{"id":21,"text":"led by Chairwoman Dianne Feinstein , California Democrat ,","depth":8},{"id":22,"text":"concluded","depth":7},{"id":23,"text":"that video cameras","depth":8},{"id":24,"text":"surrounding the compound","depth":8},{"id":25,"text":"show no spontaneous protest against the film .","depth":7},{"id":26,"text":"They also flatly concluded","depth":7},{"id":27,"text":"that fighters loyal to groups with ties to al Qaeda took part in the attack .","depth":7},{"id":28,"text":"\" Individuals","depth":9},{"id":29,"text":"affiliated with terrorist groups ,","depth":10},{"id":30,"text":"including AQIM , Ansar al-Sharia , AQAP , and the Mohammad Jamal Network ,","depth":10},{"id":31,"text":"participated in the September 11 , 2012 , attacks , \"","depth":8},{"id":32,"text":"the committee said ,","depth":8},{"id":33,"text":"using the acronyms for al Qaeda in the Islamic Maghreb and al Qaeda in the Arabian Peninsula .","depth":8},{"id":34,"text":"SEE ALSO :","depth":4},{"id":35,"text":"Michele Bachmann :","depth":5},{"id":36,"text":"Benghazi report a ' very grim picture for America '","depth":5},{"id":37,"text":"The committee report exposed abysmal security at the Benghazi outpost ,","depth":7},{"id":38,"text":"including evidence","depth":8},{"id":39,"text":"that some of the local guards","depth":10},{"id":40,"text":"hired","depth":11},{"id":41,"text":"to protect the facility","depth":11},{"id":42,"text":"were seen vandalizing or attacking the building in the months before the assault .","depth":9},{"id":43,"text":"Those conclusions could cause political problems for former Secretary of State Hillary Rodham Clinton","depth":7},{"id":44,"text":"- though the main report doesn ' t mention her","depth":8},{"id":45,"text":"and instead places blame for the security lapses on those further down the chain of command .","depth":8},{"id":46,"text":"Mrs. Clinton has tangled heatedly with congressional Republicans over the handling of the attack and its aftermath .","depth":6},{"id":47,"text":"In an appendix to the report","depth":8},{"id":48,"text":"signed only by Sen. Saxby Chambliss of Georgia , the committee ' s vice chairman , and five fellow Republicans , the Democratic front-runner for 2016 was directly criticized for her role in the Benghazi affair .","depth":8},{"id":49,"text":"The Republican lawmakers wrote ,","depth":8},{"id":50,"text":"\" the final responsibility for security at diplomatic facilities lies with the former Secretary of State , Hillary Clinton .","depth":9},{"id":51,"text":"... At the end of the day , she was responsible","depth":11},{"id":52,"text":"for ensuring the safety of all Americans","depth":12},{"id":53,"text":"serving in our diplomatic facilities .","depth":12},{"id":54,"text":"Her failure","depth":12},{"id":55,"text":"to do so","depth":12},{"id":56,"text":"clearly made a difference in the lives of the four murdered Americans and their families . \"","depth":11},{"id":57,"text":"Despite President Obama ' s promise","depth":8},{"id":58,"text":"to take action ,","depth":8},{"id":59,"text":"nobody has been arrested","depth":7},{"id":60,"text":"as a result of the attack .","depth":6},{"id":61,"text":"Intelligence committee members said","depth":8},{"id":62,"text":"part of the problem is that the Libyan government \" has not shown the political incentive or will \"","depth":9},{"id":63,"text":"to go after those responsible for the attack ,","depth":9},{"id":64,"text":"and locals in Benghazi","depth":9},{"id":65,"text":"who have aided the U.S.","depth":9},{"id":66,"text":"have regularly turned up dead .","depth":8},{"id":67,"text":"As many as 15 people","depth":9},{"id":68,"text":"who supported the investigation or otherwise helped the U.S.","depth":9},{"id":69,"text":"have been killed since the attack ,","depth":8},{"id":70,"text":"according to the FBI .","depth":7},{"id":71,"text":"The State Department said","depth":6},{"id":72,"text":"it has taken steps","depth":7},{"id":73,"text":"to fix security problems at outposts around the globe .","depth":7},{"id":74,"text":"But spokeswoman Marie Harf said","depth":6},{"id":75,"text":"it ' s not clear how much more could be done in the immediate run-up to the Benghazi assault","depth":7},{"id":76,"text":"because no specific intelligence alert had been issued .","depth":7},{"id":77,"text":"\" Clearly , we needed to do more with security here .","depth":6},{"id":78,"text":"Nobody is saying","depth":8},{"id":79,"text":"that we did everything perfectly by any stretch of the imagination , \"","depth":8},{"id":80,"text":"she said .","depth":7},{"id":81,"text":"\" But again , we continue to assess","depth":7},{"id":82,"text":"and have no information","depth":8},{"id":83,"text":"to indicate","depth":9},{"id":84,"text":"that there was any significant preplanning involved here .","depth":9},{"id":85,"text":"So there was a situation","depth":7},{"id":86,"text":"where it looks like bad guys","depth":9},{"id":87,"text":"who were already operating there","depth":9},{"id":88,"text":"took advantage of a situation . \"","depth":8},{"id":89,"text":"The report tries to correct some of the narrative","depth":4},{"id":90,"text":"that has emerged since the attack .","depth":4},{"id":91,"text":"For example , committee members said","depth":4},{"id":92,"text":"that contrary to reports , the U.S. was not the only country","depth":6},{"id":93,"text":"to keep its mission in Benghazi open during the summer of 2012","depth":6},{"id":94,"text":"- a claim","depth":7},{"id":95,"text":"some administration critics made","depth":7},{"id":96,"text":"in questioning","depth":7},{"id":97,"text":"why the American outpost remained in such a dangerous place .","depth":7},{"id":98,"text":"The report also clears the military of a number of accusations ,","depth":5},{"id":99,"text":"including that commanders blocked a relief effort","depth":6},{"id":100,"text":"and failed to get assets moving quickly enough .","depth":6},{"id":101,"text":"Investigators concluded","depth":6},{"id":102,"text":"that troops or aircraft","depth":8},{"id":103,"text":"that could have helped in that kind of situation","depth":8},{"id":104,"text":"were stationed too far away","depth":8},{"id":105,"text":"to come to the rescue .","depth":8},{"id":106,"text":"In one stark revelation , the investigators said","depth":6},{"id":107,"text":"Gen. Carter Ham ,","depth":10},{"id":108,"text":"who was in charge of U.S. Africa Command at the time ,","depth":10},{"id":109,"text":"offered Mr. Stevens more security","depth":10},{"id":110,"text":"by extending the deployment of a military site security team .","depth":10},{"id":111,"text":"The State Department had declined the extension ,","depth":9},{"id":112,"text":"but Gen. Ham ,","depth":11},{"id":113,"text":"after reading intelligence warnings ,","depth":11},{"id":114,"text":"twice asked Mr. Stevens","depth":11},{"id":115,"text":"whether he wanted the site security team to remain .","depth":11},{"id":116,"text":"The ambassador declined both offers .","depth":7},{"id":117,"text":"Republicans on the committee joined in the report ' s conclusions","depth":6},{"id":118,"text":"but submitted an addendum","depth":7},{"id":119,"text":"saying","depth":8},{"id":120,"text":"the findings didn ' t go far enough .","depth":8},{"id":121,"text":"The Republican senators said","depth":8},{"id":122,"text":"the administration is still stonewalling a request for some documents","depth":9},{"id":123,"text":"and that some State Department officials","depth":11},{"id":124,"text":"involved in decision-making","depth":11},{"id":125,"text":"have refused to testify .","depth":10},{"id":126,"text":"Others gave testimony","depth":9},{"id":127,"text":"that contradicted written documents","depth":9},{"id":128,"text":"or , in the case of Undersecretary of State for Management Patrick Kennedy , gave testimony","depth":9},{"id":129,"text":"that","depth":11},{"id":130,"text":"the senators said","depth":11},{"id":131,"text":"\" was particularly specious . \"","depth":10},{"id":132,"text":"\" The Obama administration was more of a roadblock than a contributor , \"","depth":7},{"id":133,"text":"said Sen. Marco Rubio , Florida Republican and intelligence committee member .","depth":7},{"id":134,"text":"Republicans also criticized the report","depth":6},{"id":135,"text":"for not paying more attention to the role of White House and State Department officials","depth":7},{"id":136,"text":"who pushed the intelligence community to blame protests rather than a coordinated terrorist assault .","depth":7},{"id":137,"text":"\" It is baffling how a fundamental , unclassified fact","depth":9},{"id":138,"text":"that was known to the [ intelligence community ] from the beginning","depth":9},{"id":139,"text":"was only communicated clearly to the American people by the administration","depth":8},{"id":140,"text":"after the issue had already been sufficiently muddled","depth":8},{"id":141,"text":"to result in confusion , \"","depth":8},{"id":142,"text":"said Sen. Susan M. Collins , Maine Republican and a member of the committee .","depth":6}],"relations":[{"parent":285,"left":231,"right":284,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":231,"left":179,"right":230,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":179,"left":176,"right":178,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":176,"left":162,"right":175,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":162,"left":156,"right":161,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":156,"left":148,"right":155,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":148,"left":0,"right":147,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":147,"left":144,"right":146,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":144,"left":1,"right":2,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":146,"left":145,"right":5,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":145,"left":3,"right":4,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":155,"left":152,"right":154,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":152,"left":6,"right":151,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":151,"left":149,"right":150,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":149,"left":7,"right":8,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":150,"left":9,"right":10,"relation":"condition","nuclearity":"NS"},{"p